node.text:
Welcome back to The Simonetta Lein Show. Today's episode will be extremely special as I premier my 3rd Season Finale, with a very honorable guest! Please join me in welcoming American singer-songwriter, rapper, record producer, and entrepreneur, @CeeloGreen. You all know the Grammy award-winning artist for the hit tracks “Fool for You”, and of course one of the most famous songs of contemporary music, “Fuck You.” Ceelo has worked with industry legends for decades, from @OutKast to @xtina, and continues to create as he releases his newest single, “Baby Don’t You Go-Go'' as part of his newest project called DCeeLo & DMV – Dance Music Vibration, which is in honor of and inspired by Go-Go Music. Today, Ceelo and I talk all things music, how his career started, the evolution of the industry, and he even shared some advice for the aspiring entrepreneurs and artists listening! Please join me in closing Season 3 of The Simonetta Lein Show by welcoming... Ceelo Green! 📺

Fun Facts: I just missed Ceelo while vacationing in Miami, but he promised to take me scuba diving if I come back! One of the most fulfilling aspects of Ceelos's career is mentoring emerging artists, as he has on @nbcthevoice. See you in September for SEASON 4!!!✨✨✨

Thank you to the beautifully dedicated SLTV team & ALL our fans who have joined us for another great season!

🎞Executive Producer: Raphael Amabile 
🎥Production Manager: Kate Massih @klmassih 
📞Booking Producer: James Clark @clark_public_relations
💆🏼‍♀️Hair: Jeannine Roach @beautybyjeannine
💄MUA: Nicole Patrick @nicolepatrickmua  @thebeautybarandlounge

Welcome back to The Simonetta Lein Show. Today's episode will be very heartfelt as I welcome actress, writer, host, and fashion designer, @haylieduff. Not only does Haylie star on the big screen and produced her own content, but she also entered the world of cooking about 10 years ago. What started out as a blog turned into an entire cookbook and cooking channel series. Haylie sat down with me today to discuss growing up in the spotlight, the changes that come with motherhood, and even some of her newest projects!... Tune In 📺✨

Fun Facts: Haylie & I both miss the days growing up without social media, although it has allowed us to share with our fans today. Haylie said, just about everything changed for her the day she became a mother. Lastly, Haylie hinted at a possible new project she is beginning to work on with a friend for the coming years! We are talking about serious cooking as well!

Thank you to the beautifully dedicated #SLTV team!
 
🎞Executive Producer: Raphael Amabile 
🎥Production Manager: Kate Massih @klmassih 
📞Booking Producer: James Clark @clark_public_relations
💄MUA & 💆🏼‍♀️Hair: Kortnie Figura @makeupkort

node.text:
Welcome back to The Simonetta Lein Show. Today's episode is filled with inspiration, as I introduce my very first fashion panel, with two amazing guests, renowned fashion designer Julien Macdonald @julienmacdonald and fashion icon Gabriela Gonzalez @gabrielagonzalezofficial! The two dear friends have joined me today to discuss all things fashion, from how they met, to Julien's early career, which includes becoming the protege for @karllagerfeld and working for top houses of @chanel, @givenchy, and @fendi. Julien and Gabriela eventually went on to design a joint line together @julienxgabriela, which has now been worn by some of the world's biggest names. They even gave me a sneak peek into an upcoming second collaboration! This is a glamorous episode you won't want to miss...Tune In 📺✨

Fun Facts: Julien, Gabriela, and I all called in from different time zones, from Mexico to Philly to London! Julien earned his passion for knitwear at a young age, growing up with his mother and sisters, allowing him to stand out from other designers. Gabriela and Julien fell into collaboration almost by accident, as she ultimately became his muse and she always added her own flare to the designs he originally made her. 

Thank you to the beautifully dedicated SLTV team!
 
🎞Executive Producer: Raphael Amabile 
🎥Production Manager: Kate Massih @klmassih 
📞Booking Producer: James Clark @clark_public_relations
💄MUA & 💆🏼‍♀️Hair: Kortnie Figura @makeupkort

Welcome back to The Simonetta Lein Show. Today’s episode will be very upbeat and exciting as I welcome Los Angeles’ very own Joseph Foreman, better known as Afroman @ogafroman! A Grammy-nominated, American rapper, singer, songwriter, and multi-instrumentalist, Joseph, is known for his songs "Because I Got High" and "Crazy Rap", which were featured on his album, The Good Times. He has worked with some of the industry’s biggest names, possibly one of the biggest being hip-hop legend @snoopdogg. With his multi-decade-long career, he continues to perform for his dedicated fan bases with his classic hits. Afroman joins me today to talk about all things music and his early career, how he feels the music industry has changed over the decades, and what his infamous hit, "Because I Got High" means to him today. It is an inspiring and fun episode you won't want to miss! Tune in...📺✨

Fun Facts: We both miss the old-school days of rap when rhyme was the real name of the game and cassettes kept music alive! My husband used to sing Afroman's hit "Because I Got High" to me all the time making it a household favorite. Afroman shared that when he gets called a one-hit-wonder regardless of his extensive career, all he has to say is, "How many hits do ya need?" It only takes one to open the doors!

Thank you to the beautifully dedicated SLTV team!

Welcome back to The Simonetta Lein Show. Today’s episode will be very enlightening, especially for our young businessmen and women watching, as we welcome American entrepreneur, CEO of @cardonecapital, & business consultant, @discovery Channel’s Undercover Billionaire star, and New York Times best-selling author of the 10x Rule, Grant Cardone! @grantcardone is a renowned master salesperson whose passion is to teach people how to sell themselves, their products, and their services regardless of the economic climate. Recently, Grant has steered his energy toward his social media presence, in order to directly connect with his fanbases and provide career and financial advice on a much more personal level, which led him to join me on today's episode! Grant and I talk all things business from his earliest career endeavors to his thoughts on the young labor forces of today and the infamous "grind culture". If you're looking for inspiration and information on how to jump start or continue growing your business or financial career, this is the episode for you! Tune in...📺✨

Fun Facts: Grant & I were both originally taught to avoid business partners early on in our careers, but ultimately pushed past this to find true success, you need a team! We also don't believe in excuses. Just like Cardone's #UndercoverBillionaire series, you can start with nothing and build everything for yourself with the right mindset. Hopefully, you'll see us posting pics together soon in front of his giant gorilla portrait and smoking cigars in Miami! 

Thank you to the beautifully dedicated SLTV team!

Welcome back to The Simonetta Lein Show. I am so excited to present our 8th consecutive game-changing entrepreneurs panel and very first celebrity co-hosted segment with returning guest, Shark-Tank’s Kevin Harrington @realkevinharrington! Kevin joined me to give premier business advice and industry insight to this month's panelists.

Today I welcome, Kim Constable @TheSculptedVegan, CEO & Founder of The Sculpted Vegan, a premier bodybuilding and fitness brand, Junior Anthony @junioranthonylive,  Founder and CEO of Livesotori @livesotori, a financial consultation brand, and Sophie Bowman @sophiecbowman, a Forbes published multi-award-winning entrepreneur and social media guru. You won't want to miss Kevin's expert feedback as he joins us this episode...Tune In 📺✨ 

Fun Facts: Sophie and Thomas are two returning panelists, excited to catch us up on their newest business ventures! Both Kim and Sophie have dedicated parts of their careers to Bikini Fitness Modeling and started both at 37! Shameca and Junior are all about building and sharing wealth and the secrets to success, it's more than just numbers but your mental state too! As well Junior has an amazing personal story, from homeless to Millionaire! Dedrick is ahead of the growing e-commerce game and focusing on i-commerce, the future of retail! Kevin advise at the end is priceless!

Thank you to the beautifully dedicated SLTV team!

Welcome back to The Simonetta Lein Show. Today’s episode will be very inspiring as we welcome the creator, star, and executive producer of @paramountnetwork's @barrescuetv, Jon Taffer @jontaffer. For over four decades, Taffer has been at the forefront of the business management industry offering his expertise to hundreds of thousands of properties and Fortune 500 companies. He is a New York Times best-selling author who takes a no-holds-barred approach to helping hotels, restaurants, bars, and businesses reach their full potential. I had the pleasure of speaking with Jon about his journey into becoming a reality TV star and celebrity business consultant. Jon also shared with me the importance of authentic content and the need to understand the psychological roots of a failed business. It is an episode you won't want to miss! Tune in...📺✨

Fun Facts: Jon & I both stress the core of success is credited to a healthy mindset. Both of us are always up for a fight as conflict leads to true solutions. As two TV hosts, we believe good content always comes from authenticity. He even invited me to do a podcast live from Las Vegas!

Welcome back to The Simonetta Lein Show. Today’s episode will be very inspiring as we welcome Grammy Award Nominated musician, singer-songwriter, producer, humanitarian, and son of reggae legend @bobmarley, Julian Marley @julianrmarley. During Julian’s earliest years in Jamaica, he began to study under legendary reggae veterans, along with his own father’s inspiration, such as the Barrett Brothers @famsbass and Earl Lindo, to eventually work his way up to collaborating with the legend that is @mslaurynhill . In the same tradition as his father, Julian is a devout Rastafarian whose music is inspired by life and spirituality, as he continues to embark on his life missions. Julien joins me today to discuss his early life, growing up under the wing of his father's legacy, the spiritual and moral conflicts of our world today, and his personal love for music. This is a magical episode you won't want to miss! Tune in...📺✨

Fun Facts: My husband and I are some of the biggest old-school reggae fans, having listened to everyone from Bob Marley to Sister Carol! During the interview I mentioned several of my favorite quotes from @bobmarley as I live by them

Thank you to the beautifully dedicated SLTV team!

Welcome back to The Simonetta Lein Show. Today’s episode will be joyful and uplifting as I welcome, actor, singer, producer and television personality Kalen Allen @thekalenallen, whose career has continued to skyrocket, after his viral internet content earned him, and his signature red hat, a regular guest spot on “The Ellen DeGeneres Show” @theellenshow. Originally from Kansas City, Kalen attended our very own Temple University in Philadelphia and graduated with a Bachelor of Arts in Theatre. He actively supports The Point Foundation @pointfoundation, which empowers aspiring LGBTQ+ individuals to achieve their full academic and leadership potential. Today, Kalen joins me to discuss his experience joining the Ellen show, his journey with fashion as a form of self-expression, what it's like growing up in the spotlight, and his work to support the LGBTQ+ community. Tune in...📺✨

Fun Facts: Kalen is one of our very own, a Philly native, having attending Temple University. We both have a passion for fashion and a knack for TV hosting! So sweet to hear him talking about his first meeting with @oprah as she knew all of his videos as a true fan, or being inspired so much and mentored by @michelleobama and his collaborative video with @mariahcarey for the "All I Want For Christmas Is You" 25th anniversary edition.

Thank you to the beautifully dedicated SLTV team!

Welcome back to The Simonetta Lein Show. Today's episode will be full of laughs as I introduce my very first comedy panel with guest stars Kev On Stage @kevonstage & Sam Morril @sammorril. Kevin has turned himself into a household name and grown his fanbase into a booming digital media company and even created a Kev On Stage App, to bring viewers the greatest in digital Black content from artists they know and love. He has developed and hosted several popular podcasts and even independently produced The Real Comedians of Social Media tour and the series, "Keep Your Distance". Sam Morril has been a regular on @comedycentral and was the host of his very own show on MSG, receiving an Emmy® nomination and also appeared in the Academy Award-nominated film, Joker. He has been on @colbertlateshow and @latelateshow numerous times. In 2020, Morril released 2 successful stand-up specials including Comedy Central’s “I Got This” and his most recent segment, “Up On The Roof Top.”

Fun Facts: Kevin and Sam actually met for the first time on my show! We each have ventured into the independent production and distribution of our content, and we all can't wait to be back and working in person!

Thank you to the beautifully dedicated SLTV team!
 
🎞Executive Producer: Raphael Amabile 
🎥Production Manager: Kate Massih @klmassih 
📞Booking Producer: James Clark @clark_public_relations

Welcome back to The Simonetta Lein Show. Today's episode will be extremely special as I premier my 3rd Season Finale, with a very honorable guest! Please join me in welcoming American singer-songwriter, rapper, record producer, and entrepreneur, @CeeloGreen. You all know the Grammy award-winning artist for the hit tracks “Fool for You”, and of course one of the most famous songs of contemporary music, “Fuck You.” Ceelo has worked with industry legends for decades, from @OutKast to @xtina, and continues to create as he releases his newest single, “Baby Don’t You Go-Go'' as part of his newest project called DCeeLo & DMV – Dance Music Vibration, which is in honor of and inspired by Go-Go Music. Today, Ceelo and I talk all things music, how his career started, the evolution of the industry, and he even shared some advice for the aspiring entrepreneurs and artists listening! Please join me in closing Season 3 of The Simonetta Lein Show by welcoming... Ceelo Green! 📺

Fun Facts: I just missed Ceelo while vacationing in Miami, but he promised to take me scuba diving if I come back! One of the most fulfilling aspects of Ceelos's career is mentoring emerging artists, as he has on @nbcthevoice. See you in September for SEASON 4!!!✨✨✨

Thank you to the beautifully dedicated SLTV team & ALL our fans who have joined us for another great season!

Welcome back to The Simonetta Lein Show. Today's episode will be very heartfelt as I welcome actress, writer, host, and fashion designer, @haylieduff. Not only does Haylie star on the big screen and produced her own content, but she also entered the world of cooking about 10 years ago. What started out as a blog turned into an entire cookbook and cooking channel series. Haylie sat down with me today to discuss growing up in the spotlight, the changes that come with motherhood, and even some of her newest projects!... Tune In 📺✨

Fun Facts: Haylie & I both miss the days growing up without social media, although it has allowed us to share with our fans today. Haylie said, just about everything changed for her the day she became a mother. Lastly, Haylie hinted at a possible new project she is beginning to work on with a friend for the coming years! We are talking about serious cooking as well!

Thank you to the beautifully dedicated #SLTV team!

If I have to go to work to NY I never miss it to make it fun and eating back in the city, after all that happen and walking with my dog down the streets gave me much joy. 
The same showroom opened up now in Miami so all the designers you see me wearing for this cover story are NY vibes in Miami, bringing the best of the worlds of fashion at the moment.

Welcome back to The Simonetta Lein Show. Today's episode is filled with inspiration, as I introduce my very first fashion panel, with two amazing guests, renowned fashion designer Julien Macdonald @julienmacdonald and fashion icon Gabriela Gonzalez @gabrielagonzalezofficial! The two dear friends have joined me today to discuss all things fashion, from how they met, to Julien's early career, which includes becoming the protege for @karllagerfeld and working for top houses of @chanel, @givenchy, and @fendi. Julien and Gabriela eventually went on to design a joint line together @julienxgabriela, which has now been worn by some of the world's biggest names. They even gave me a sneak peek into an upcoming second collaboration! This is a glamorous episode you won't want to miss...Tune In 📺✨

Fun Facts: Julien, Gabriela, and I all called in from different time zones, from Mexico to Philly to London! Julien earned his passion for knitwear at a young age, growing up with his mother and sisters, allowing him to stand out from other designers. Gabriela and Julien fell into collaboration almost by accident, as she ultimately became his muse and she always added her own flare to the designs he originally made her. 

Thank you to the beautifully dedicated SLTV team!

Do it big style or don’t do it at all 💅
.

Do you have your own idol or just a person to look up to?
My husband is my hero. He is always there and there is nothing he cannot do. He doesn’t push back and I owe anything I do to him our team. 

What are your plans for the future?
I have learned to live day by day but I am looking up to some huge names that we are booking on the show to interview. I cannot share who they are, you will have to watch it yourself but they are all A listers and I am a big fan of all of them.

Tell us a little about your career in New York.
Modeling at Madison Square Garden and NY Fashion Week are an intrinsic part of my history. Doing a show for designer Richie Rich and opening the show for Stevie Boi right before the all world would stop is my New York story of representing. We pull the best clothes out of New York. We just do it big style or we don’t do it at all. 

How do you feel about fashion? Have you attended New York Fashion Week? If you have visited, please tell us about your impressions.
Fashion is resilient. I haven’t visited fashion week since February 2020 when I opened the Stevie Boi Show. Will be back for sure.

node.text:
It truly takes a village to make it all happen.
Dedicated to all the people behind the scene who works hard!
.
My cover story is on @mynewyorkmag
.
Tell us more about your show.

We are at Third Season and rocking it towards the second half and soon, towards the end of the Summer, the Forth Season will start. I still cannot believe it! We have the biggest stars and the most unique content. My team is amazing, it truly takes a village to make it all happen.

How did you come up with the idea to create your own project?

I actually was asked by a production company in NY to create The Simonetta Lein Show. When quarantine hit, last year everything stopped so we had to refocus and re start and instead of stopping it we made it even bigger and better: that is such a New Yorker attitude that my husband - a New Yorker - taught me. We never stop.

Is it difficult to be an influencer today?

The world has changed. The world is saturated so it is the real opportunity to shine and to be completely unique or you’ll be just one of the many. In order to do that it is time to go the extra mile and create your own projects and create the best team you can possibly have. So important. The team work makes the dream work.

Welcome back to The Simonetta Lein Show. Today’s episode will be very upbeat and exciting as I welcome Los Angeles’ very own Joseph Foreman, better known as Afroman @ogafroman! He has worked with some of the industry’s biggest names, possibly one of the biggest being hip-hop legend @snoopdogg. With his multi-decade-long career, he continues to perform for his dedicated fan bases with his classic hits. Afroman joins me today to talk about all things music and his early career, how he feels the music industry has changed over the decades, and what his infamous hit, "Because I Got High" means to him today. It is an inspiring and fun episode you won't want to miss! Tune in...📺✨

Fun Facts: We both miss the old-school days of rap when rhyme was the real name of the game and cassettes kept music alive! My husband used to sing Afroman's hit "Because I Got High" to me all the time making it a household favorite. Afroman shared that when he gets called a one-hit-wonder regardless of his extensive career, all he has to say is, "How many hits do ya need?" It only takes one to open the doors!

Know Your Power 💅
.
7.Where should a beginner start if they want to follow in your footsteps?

Find a side job and put some money aside. With that, hire a good photographer, hair and makeup artists. Make sure your outfits stand out. Start posting on social media. Boost your social media with some marketing company that can help your posts be seen on the explorer page. There are packages as little as $50 a month so it is totally doable even if you are very young. Google them. Reach out to brands trying to close collaborations. The more you grow your name, the more it would be easier for brands to reply to you and want to work with you.  Try to be part of projects with other models or designers, differentiate yourself. The first paid job will come and from there many more. Invest in yourself, in your brand. You have to stand out from the pack. If everyone is going in one direction, you want to be the one who goes the opposite way. 

8. What do you dream about?

I dream about some daily peace. We are bombarded with negative news, people just need to have their serene daily life. I dream about seeing my parents who are in Italy. It has been too long. Those simple things. God is good and we have to follow his timing. I just pray every day so that the light will overcome the dark.
.
